#Approach:

Approach (Hinglish) – Minimum Number of Days to Make m Bouquets (Binary Search on Answer)

Is question mein hume minimum day find karna hai
jisme hum m bouquets bana sakein,
aur har bouquet ke liye k adjacent flowers chahiye.

Brute force mein hum har day check kar sakte hain,
lekin bloomDay[i] bahut bada ho sakta hai,
isliye Binary Search on Answer use karenge.

Key Idea:
Answer hamesha minimum bloom day se maximum bloom day ke beech hoga.

Agar kisi day "mid" tak hum m ya usse zyada bouquets bana sakte hain,
to ho sakta hai answer usse bhi chhota ho.
Isliye left side search karenge.

Agar kisi day "mid" tak m bouquets nahi ban paa rahe,
to aur zyada days wait karna padega.
Isliye right side search karenge.

Important impossible case:
Agar total required flowers = m * k
aur wo garden ke total flowers se zyada hain,
to answer kabhi possible hi nahi hoga.
Isliye directly -1 return kar do.

How helper works:
Helper check karta hai ki given day "mid" tak
kya hum m bouquets bana sakte hain ya nahi.

Logic:
1. Array traverse karo
2. Agar bloomDay[i] <= mid hai,
   matlab flower bloom ho chuka hai -> cnt++
3. Agar bloomDay[i] > mid hai,
   matlab sequence break ho gaya
   -> cnt / k jitne bouquets ban sakte the wo add karo
   -> cnt = 0
4. Loop ke end par bhi cnt / k add karna zaroori hai
5. Agar total bouquets >= m
   -> possible
   else -> not possible

Why cnt / k?
Kyuki hume k adjacent flowers chahiye.
Agar consecutive bloomed flowers ka count cnt hai,
to unse cnt / k bouquets ban sakte hain.

Example:
cnt = 7, k = 3
To bouquets = 7 / 3 = 2

Steps:
1. Agar (long)m * k > bloomDay.length
   -> return -1

2. low = minimum bloom day
   high = maximum bloom day

3. mid = (low + high) / 2

4. Check karo mid day tak bouquets possible hain ya nahi

5. Agar possible hai
   -> aur minimum day chahiye
   -> high = mid - 1

6. Else
   -> aur zyada days chahiye
   -> low = mid + 1

Loop ke end par low minimum valid day hota hai.

Why return low?
Kyuki binary search ke baad low first aisa day hota hai
jahan m bouquets banana possible hota hai.

Time Complexity:
mini() -> O(n)
maxi() -> O(n)
helper() -> O(n)
Binary Search -> O(log(maxDay - minDay))
Total -> O(n * log(maxDay - minDay))

Space Complexity:
O(1)

One line intuition:
Minimum aisa day find karna hai jahan tak enough adjacent bloomed flowers mil jaayein
taaki m bouquets ban sakein, isliye answer space par binary search lagate hain.

#Code:

class Solution {

    public int mini(int[] bloomDay){
        int n = bloomDay.length;
        int minVal = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            minVal = Math.min(minVal, bloomDay[i]);
        }
        return minVal;
    }
    public int maxi(int[] bloomDay){
        int n = bloomDay.length;
        int maxVal = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            maxVal = Math.max(maxVal, bloomDay[i]);
        }
        return maxVal;
    }

    public int helper(int[] bloomDay, int m, int k, int mid){
        int cnt = 0;
        int noOfBouquet = 0;
        int n = bloomDay.length;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            if(bloomDay[i] <= mid){
                cnt++;
            }
            else{
                noOfBouquet += cnt/k;
                cnt = 0;
            }
        }
        //check if there is any possibility of becoming a bouquet
        noOfBouquet += cnt/k;
        if(noOfBouquet >= m){
            return 1;
        }else{
            return 0;
        }
    }

    public int minDays(int[] bloomDay, int m, int k) {
        
        if((long)m*k > bloomDay.length) return -1;
        int low = mini(bloomDay);
        int high = maxi(bloomDay);

        while(low <= high){
            int mid = (low + high)/2;
            int val = helper(bloomDay, m, k, mid);

            if(val == 1){
                high = mid-1;
            }
            else{
                low = mid+1;
            }
        }
        return low;

        
    }
}
